    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cylindrical outdoor sidewalk structures used as supports for printed advertising for theatrical and other entertainments. The invention is  attributed to Gabriel Morris ca. 1868 in the city of Paris, though earlier advertising pillars were erected in Berlin in the 1850s, created by printer Ernst Litfass.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
